From e0baa6cf3f0710a63b54ceca103c0f2c961f4f87 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mavis <Mavis@mavis.local>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 22:44:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: stop wiping cached downloads on activity recreation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

cleanPapraCache() ran unconditionally in MainActivity.onCreate(), which fires
on every configuration change (rotation, theme switch, font scale) and after
process death + restart. It deleted papra_* files from cacheDir while the
PDF/image viewer was still trying to read them, producing 'Cannot open this PDF',
'Failed to load image', and the 'Failed to open document' snackbar in
DocumentsScreen when reopening.

Additional fixes in the same area:

- downloadDocumentToCache() now rejects null/zero-byte response bodies and
  cleans up partial files on IOException, so the viewer never gets handed a
  Success result for a 0-byte file (which silently broke PdfRenderer /
  BitmapFactory.decodeFile).
- PdfViewerScreen + ImageViewerScreen detect missing/empty files up front and
  show a clear 'file no longer cached, go back and reopen' message instead of
  trying to render a non-existent file or crashing FileProvider.getUriForFile().
- Replaced cleanPapraCache() with trimPapraCache(maxBytes=50MB) — LRU eviction
  based on lastModified, no-op under the cap, called only after a successful
  download. Bound is checked against total papra_* file sizes; oldest first.

Build verified: ./gradlew assembleDebug → BUILD SUCCESSFUL.
